n the communities associated with B. azoricus. Distinct patterns of abundances and diversity were observed across the three fields, with MG appearing as a particular case. The presence of a longitudinal current to the south of this field and its depth difference may partially explain those discrepancies. This study represents one of the most comprehensive integrated faunal and environmental datasets obtained across hydrothermal vent fields.},
